{{!< default}}

<section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-center">
        <div class="hero-eyebrow">A Nozomi Content Series</div>
        <h1 class="hero-title">The Last Decade of <span class="accent-word">Freedom</span></h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle">Beyond the scams and speculation. <strong>Decentralisation is the last stand of true freedom</strong>, where self-sovereignty survives against centralisation and corruption. Weekly deep dives on the real case for crypto, startup ideas, and what builders should be building next.</p>

        <form class="hero-form" data-members-form="signup">
            <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Your email address" required />
            <button type="submit">Get Access</button>
        </form>
        <p class="hero-fineprint">Free. No spam. Unsubscribe anytime.</p>
        <div class="hero-ornament">望</div>
    </div>
</section>

{{!-- Why this series exists --}}
<section class="prose-section">
    <div class="prose-block">
        <div class="section-label">Why this series exists</div>
        <p>The next decade decides humanity's future. AI, robotics, and brain-computer interfaces are accelerating at a pace most people do not fully grasp. Whoever controls the models controls the future. First they control your wealth. Then what you see. Then what you think. We are walking into a world where Orwell's 1984 is not fiction. It is the default trajectory.</p>
        <p>The one technology built to fight back is still dismissed as a scam. But underneath the noise, decentralisation is the most important technological movement of our lifetime. It is the only path to a world where humans are at the center and technology serves them, instead of the other way around.</p>
        <p>This newsletter exists to help the builders win. Fundraising and growth playbooks for the founders beating their Web2 competition. No hype. No token shilling. Just the real work that moves the needle, and the ideas that push the space forward.</p>
    </div>
</section>

{{!-- What You Get --}}
<section class="get-section">
    <div class="get-header">
        <div class="section-label">What You Get</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Every week in your inbox</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="get-grid">
        <div class="get-card">
            <div class="get-card-icon">📖</div>
            <h3>Deep-Dive Articles</h3>
            <p>Long-form explorations of the real problems crypto solves. No jargon, no shilling. Accessible to anyone, even if they've never bought a token.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="get-card">
            <div class="get-card-icon">🚀</div>
            <h3>Startup Ideas</h3>
            <p>Every article includes a concrete "Request for Startups". What's not yet being built, and what Nozomi would incubate and support.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="get-card">
            <div class="get-card-icon">🗺</div>
            <h3>Fundraising &amp; Growth Playbooks</h3>
            <p>Step-by-step implementation guides to help founders plan, raise, and launch. From idea to TGE and beyond, with frameworks you can action immediately.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

{{!-- The Series --}}
<section class="series-section">
    <div class="series-header">
        <div class="section-label">The Series</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">One series. Two parallel tracks.</h2>
        <p class="series-tagline">Part 1 answers "why should I care?" Part 2 answers "what can I actually build?" Together, they convert sceptics into believers and believers into builders.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="series-tracks">
        <div class="track">
            <div class="track-label">Part 1</div>
            <h3>Verticals &amp; First Principles</h3>
            <p class="track-desc">Too many Web3 founders are giving up on the mission for scale, removing the decentralisation first principles, which just creates Web2 with worse UI/UX. This track covers the actual verticals and the ideologies needed to build decentralisation that matters.</p>
            <ul class="track-list">
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> Digital Currency &amp; Sound Money</li>
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> The Decentralised World Computer</li>
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> Decentralised AI (De-AI)</li>
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> Decentralised Storage &amp; Data Sovereignty</li>
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> Privacy-Preserving Algorithms</li>
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> Self-Sovereign Identity</li>
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> Decentralised Governance &amp; Network States</li>
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> The Cypherpunk Origin Story</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="track-count">Weekly deep dives</div>
        </div>
        <div class="track">
            <div class="track-label">Part 2</div>
            <h3>Real Use Cases &amp; Startup Ideas</h3>
            <p class="track-desc">Every article takes a real-world problem and proposes a concrete decentralised startup idea that a founder could build today. Not abstract theory. Tangible products people would actually use.</p>
            <ul class="track-list">
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> AI-simulated dating: avatars run thousands of compatibility scenarios before you ever meet, replacing mindless swiping with high-conviction matches</li>
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> Creator IP licensing on-chain: musicians, artists, and writers control and monetise their work without middlemen taking 80%</li>
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> Decentralised credit scoring: your financial reputation is portable, private, and not owned by Equifax</li>
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> Community-owned social networks: your feed, your algorithm, your data. No ads. No manipulation</li>
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> Autonomous AI agent economies: agents that trade, negotiate, and transact on your behalf across open protocols</li>
                <li><span class="track-arrow">→</span> Decentralised energy markets, supply chain provenance, and more</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="track-count">Weekly deep dives</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

{{!-- Final CTA --}}
<section class="cta-section">
    <div class="cta-inner">
        <div class="hero-ornament cta-ornament">望</div>
        <h2 class="cta-title">The next decade decides everything.</h2>
        <p class="cta-desc">Decentralisation is how we fight back. This series is the ammunition. Get it free, every week.</p>
        <form class="hero-form cta-form" data-members-form="signup">
            <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Your email address" required />
            <button type="submit">Get Access</button>
        </form>
    </div>
</section>

{{#if posts}}
<section class="letters-section">
    <h2>Latest Letters</h2>
    {{#foreach posts}}
        <article class="letter-card">
            <div class="meta">{{date published_at format="MMM DD, YYYY"}}{{#if primary_tag}} · {{primary_tag.name}}{{/if}}</div>
            <h3><a href="{{url}}">{{title}}</a></h3>
            {{#if excerpt}}<p class="excerpt">{{excerpt words="28"}}</p>{{/if}}
            <span class="read">{{reading_time}} · <a href="{{url}}">Read letter →</a></span>
        </article>
    {{/foreach}}
</section>
{{/if}}
